a cold morning by the sea

My 2022. 
~ ~ ~ ~
A full year to be myself and get out there and experience life without any limitations or anything holding me back.
•
In February, I decided to travel alone to Iceland and this changed my life and my entire mental state. I came back a more confident person with a mindset of being content by myself. Being alone in another country really makes you figure out really quick who you are as a person. Highly recommend doing this if you're ever able to.
•
In June, I decided to be more social and do something completely random. I wanted to join a couple photographer friends I've known from Instagram/Twitter and do an RV trip with them in Wyoming/Montana. Severe weather altered the trip a bit, but I was able to see the beautiful Grand Tetons in Wyoming and the Salt Flats in Utah.
•
In September, I had a work trip in California and decided to make a solo trip (second ever) of that so I drove from the Terrenea resort up to visit Sequoia National Park and Yosemite National Park. Saw some amazing sights in the parks.
•
In October, decided to trek it to upstate New York to meet some other photographer friends and shoot some fall foliage with them. More amazing views and memories I'll never forget.
•
It was for sure a year l'Il never forget and will always look back on as the year I was able to fully discover myself.
Excited for 2023 trips I have planned and whatever the future holds for me
